<subSubSection id="C30D650EBE48FFC7FF55BD8E83820135" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA83685BE48FFC7FF55BD8E812C06BA" blockId="10.[189,363,725,751]" box="[189,363,725,751]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
<heading id="D0E081E9BE48FFC7FF55BD8E812C06BA" bold="true" box="[189,363,725,751]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FF55BD8E812C06BA" bold="true" box="[189,363,725,751]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Redescription</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83685BE48FFC7FF55BC5F835D07A4" blockId="10.[189,1399,771,1009]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
HEAD. Both clypeus and frons uneven, provided extensively with foveae, with distinct carinae; 
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FF55BC7C809B0714" box="[189,220,807,833]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">slr</emphasis>
reaching anterior margin of frons; 
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FD7FBC7C82FE0714" box="[663,697,807,833]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">lsa</emphasis>
connecting each other, forming U-shape. Granulation of clypeus indistinct. Mandibles (
<figureCitation id="132C2A00BE48FFC7FDCCBC1182C70731" box="[548,640,842,868]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1876,1902]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,277,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[189,1398,264,1820]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Mouth parts and antennae of Georissus spp. A–C. Left maxillae. D–F. Labrum. G–I. Labial palpi. J–L. Left mandibles. M–O. Left antennae. A, D, G, J, M. G. (G.) canalifer Sharp, 1888. B, E, H, K, N. G. (Ni.) granulosus Satô, 1972. C, F, I, L, O. G. (Ne.) japonicus Satô, 1972. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Fig. 4K</figureCitation>
) relatively large; lateral margin linear, apex unidentate; mola not developed. Antennae (
<figureCitation id="132C2A00BE48FFC7FE2DBC36826607D2" box="[453,545,877,903]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1876,1902]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,277,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[189,1398,264,1820]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Mouth parts and antennae of Georissus spp. A–C. Left maxillae. D–F. Labrum. G–I. Labial palpi. J–L. Left mandibles. M–O. Left antennae. A, D, G, J, M. G. (G.) canalifer Sharp, 1888. B, E, H, K, N. G. (Ni.) granulosus Satô, 1972. C, F, I, L, O. G. (Ne.) japonicus Satô, 1972. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Fig. 4N</figureCitation>
) relatively short; antennomere 4 as wide as antennomere 3, about twice as long as antennomere 3; pubescence of club short. Labrum (
<figureCitation id="132C2A00BE48FFC7FC5CBCCB844807FF" box="[948,1039,912,938]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1876,1902]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,277,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[189,1398,264,1820]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Mouth parts and antennae of Georissus spp. A–C. Left maxillae. D–F. Labrum. G–I. Labial palpi. J–L. Left mandibles. M–O. Left antennae. A, D, G, J, M. G. (G.) canalifer Sharp, 1888. B, E, H, K, N. G. (Ni.) granulosus Satô, 1972. C, F, I, L, O. G. (Ne.) japonicus Satô, 1972. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
) protruding anteriorly; spines on anterior margin indistinct. Apical labial palpomere (
<figureCitation id="132C2A00BE48FFC7FCA4BCE883ED079B" box="[844,938,947,974]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1876,1902]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,277,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[189,1398,264,1820]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Mouth parts and antennae of Georissus spp. A–C. Left maxillae. D–F. Labrum. G–I. Labial palpi. J–L. Left mandibles. M–O. Left antennae. A, D, G, J, M. G. (G.) canalifer Sharp, 1888. B, E, H, K, N. G. (Ni.) granulosus Satô, 1972. C, F, I, L, O. G. (Ne.) japonicus Satô, 1972. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
) elongated oval, densely bearing short spines. Galea (
<figureCitation id="132C2A00BE48FFC7FE83BC8C818207A4" box="[363,453,983,1009]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1876,1902]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,277,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[189,1398,264,1820]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Mouth parts and antennae of Georissus spp. A–C. Left maxillae. D–F. Labrum. G–I. Labial palpi. J–L. Left mandibles. M–O. Left antennae. A, D, G, J, M. G. (G.) canalifer Sharp, 1888. B, E, H, K, N. G. (Ni.) granulosus Satô, 1972. C, F, I, L, O. G. (Ne.) japonicus Satô, 1972. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) densely bearing short setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83685BE48FFC7FF55BB4281B50003" blockId="10.[189,1398,1048,1110]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
PRONOTUM. Half oval; lateral portion slightly projecting laterally; disc densely provided with granules; 
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FF56BB6080B20000" box="[190,245,1083,1109]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">smlg</emphasis>
distinct; without 
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FE2BBB6081AB0000" box="[451,492,1083,1109]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">sdn</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83685BE48FFC7FF55BB26817500EF" blockId="10.[189,1399,1149,1210]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">ELYTRA. Bearing four longitudinal costae consisting of granules. Humeral bulges distinct. Lateral ridges indistinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83685BE48FFC7FF55BBB984F400AE" blockId="10.[189,1203,1249,1276]" box="[189,1203,1249,1276]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
ABDOMEN. Ventrites densely bearing granules; ventrites 1–2 without 
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FC36BBB983B400AE" box="[990,1011,1250,1275]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">vt</emphasis>
and excavation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83685BE48FFC7FF55BA7883820135" blockId="10.[189,1399,1315,1377]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">MALE GENITALIA. Aedeagus elongated. Parameres as long as phallobase. Median lobe little shorter than parameres. Basal struts short. Phallobase bulbous at basal portion.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30D650EBE48FFC7FF55BAD3857402F6" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA83685BE48FFC7FF55BAD3816801F7" blockId="10.[189,303,1416,1442]" box="[189,303,1416,1442]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
<heading id="D0E081E9BE48FFC7FF55BAD3816801F7" bold="true" box="[189,303,1416,1442]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FF55BAD3816801F7" bold="true" box="[189,303,1416,1442]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83685BE48FFC7FF55BAED857402F6" blockId="10.[187,1401,1462,1700]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
This subgenus is distinguished by the combination of the following characters: pronotum provided with large granules extensively (not extensively in subgenera 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D06BE48FFC7FCD7BA8183F401A1" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[831,947,1498,1524]" class="Insecta" family="Georissidae" genus="Georissus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FCD7BA8183F401A1" box="[831,947,1498,1524]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Georissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D06BE48FFC7FC00BA8184C301A6" authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1972" box="[1000,1156,1498,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Georissidae" genus="Georissus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neogeorissus">
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FC00BA8184C301A6" box="[1000,1156,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Neogeorissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); disc of clypeus and frons provided with many carinae, granulation indistinct (in other subgenera, granulation distinct). This subgenus comprises only two species from 
<collectingCountry id="F3007615BE48FFC7FD58B97B82B5026F" box="[688,754,1568,1594]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Japan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3007615BE48FFC7FCC0B97B844B026C" box="[808,1036,1567,1594]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
: the Japanese species is 
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FAF5B97B8575026F" box="[1309,1330,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">G</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D06BE48FFC7FAA8B97B818E0208" authority="Sato, 1972" authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Georissidae" genus="Georissus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosus" subGenus="Neogeorissus">
(
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FAA2B97B8522026C" box="[1354,1381,1568,1593]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Ni</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FF55B91881790208" box="[189,318,1603,1629]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">granulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B74BE48FFC7FEAFB918818E0208" author="Sato M." box="[327,457,1603,1629]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" pagination="207 - 213" refId="ref14083" refString="Sato M. 1972. The Georissid beetles of Japan. Journal of Nagoya Women's College 18: 207 - 213." type="journal article" year="1972">Satô, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and the other species is 
<emphasis id="B963EA97BE48FFC7FD10B918834C0208" box="[760,779,1603,1629]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">G</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D06BE48FFC7FCF3B918847B0208" authority="Deleve, 1969" authorityName="Deleve" authorityYear="1969" box="[795,1084,1603,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Georissidae" genus="Georissus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biroi" subGenus="Neogeorissus">
(
